{"title_page": "KBS Radio 1", "text_new": "{{short description|South Korea radio station}}\n{{Infobox radio station\n| name = KBS Radio 1\n| branding = \n| area = [[South Korea]] <br>\u2013 near national coverage \n| airdate = '''HLKA''':<br>{{start date and age|1927|2|16}} (as JODK)<br>{{start date and age|1947||}} (as HLKA)<br>'''HLKA-SFM''': {{start date and age|1980|12|1}}\n| frequency = '''HLKA''': [[AM broadcasting|AM]] 711 [[kilohertz|kHz]]  [[#In other provinces|...more]] <br>'''HLKA-SFM''': [[FM broadcasting|FM]]: 97.3 [[megahertz|MHz]] [[#In other provinces|...more]]\n| format = [[News]], [[Talk radio|Talk]], [[Culture]], [[Sports]]\n| callsign_meaning = '''HL'''<br>'''K'''ore'''A'''\n| owner = [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]]\n| website = [http://www.kbs.co.kr/radio/1radio kbs.co.kr/radio/1radio]\n| sister_stations = [[KBS Radio 2]],<br>[[KBS Radio 3]],<br>[[KBS 1FM|KBS Classic FM]],<br>[[KBS 2FM|KBS Cool FM]]\n| webcast = [http://onair.kbs.co.kr/?sname=onair&stype=live&ch_code=21&ch_type=radioList Listen Live]\n}}\n\n'''KBS Radio 1''' is a [[South Korea]]n [[news]], [[Talk radio|talk]], [[sports]] and [[Culture|cultural]] radio channel of the [[Korean Broadcasting System]]. The network has a 24-hour broadcast dedicated to today's events reflecting Koreans.\n\nRadio 1's programs are heard nationwide; national shows originate from Seoul, with local stations providing an amount of regional programming (including local identification at the top of the hour and at 4:53 am daily) to its audience.\n\n== Stations ==\n=== Seoul, Incheon, Gyeonggi Province ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Callsign !! Frequency !! Power !! Transmitter location\n|-\n| HLKA-AM || AM 711\u3391 || 500&nbsp;kW || Sorae\n|-\n| HLKA-SFM || FM 97.3\u3392 || 10&nbsp;kW || Gwanaksan\n|}\n\n=== In other provinces ===\n* [[Chuncheon]] : FM 99.5&nbsp;MHz, AM 657&nbsp;kHz\n* Wonju : FM 97.1&nbsp;MHz, AM 1152&nbsp;kHz\n* Gangneung : FM 98.9&nbsp;MHz, AM 864&nbsp;kHz\n* Daejeon : FM 94.7&nbsp;MHz, AM 882&nbsp;kHz\n* Cheongju : FM 89.3&nbsp;MHz, AM 1062&nbsp;kHz\n* Chungju : FM 92.1&nbsp;MHz, 103.3&nbsp;MHz, FM 90.7&nbsp;MHz\n* Jeonju : FM 96.9&nbsp;MHz, AM 567&nbsp;kHz\n* Gwangju : FM 90.5&nbsp;MHz, AM 747&nbsp;kHz\n* Mokpo : FM 105.9&nbsp;MHz, AM 1467&nbsp;kHz\n* Suncheon : FM 95.7&nbsp;MHz, AM 630&nbsp;kHz\n* Daegu : FM 101.3&nbsp;MHz, AM 738&nbsp;kHz\n* Gimcheon : FM 90.7&nbsp;MHz\n* Andong : FM 90.5&nbsp;MHz, AM 963&nbsp;kHz\n* Pohang : FM 95.9&nbsp;MHz, AM 1035&nbsp;kHz\n* Busan : FM 103.7&nbsp;MHz, AM 891&nbsp;kHz\n* Ulsan : FM 90.7&nbsp;MHz, AM 1449&nbsp;kHz \n* Changwon : FM 91.7&nbsp;MHz, AM 1278&nbsp;kHz\n* Jinju : FM 90.3&nbsp;MHz, AM 1098&nbsp;kHz\n* Jeju : FM 99.1&nbsp;MHz, AM 963&nbsp;kHz\n\n== Brief history ==\nRadio 1 was originally launched as Kyeongseong Broadcasting Corporation (JODK) by the Japanese government in Korea on February 16, 1927, and later adopted the callsign HLKA in 1947 after South Korea got the HL callsign block from the International Telecommunication Union. In 1965 the name was changed to KBS Radio 1.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[KBS Radio 2]]\n* [[EBS FM]]\n* [[MBC FM4U]]\n* [[SBS Power FM]]\n* [[CBS Music FM]]\n* [[Traffic Broadcasting System]]\n* [[EBS 1TV]]\n* [[Far East Broadcasting Company]]\n\n== References ==\n* http://www.kbs.co.kr/radio/1radio/index.html\n\n[[Category:Radio stations in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Korean Broadcasting System radio networks|Radio 1]]\n[[Category:Korean-language radio stations]]\n[[Category:Radio stations established in 1965]]\n[[Category:Chinese popular culture]]\n[[Category:South Korean popular culture]]\n[[Category:News and talk radio stations]]\n\n\n{{Asia-radio-station-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|South Korea radio station}}\n{{Infobox radio station\n| name = KBS Radio 1\n| branding = \n| area = [[South Korea]] <br>\u2013 near national coverage \n| airdate = '''HLKA''':<br>{{start date and age|1927|2|16}} (as JODK)<br>{{start date and age|1947||}} (as HLKA)<br>'''HLK